summary: This is an email chain between US Attorney's Offices (likely New York and New Hampshire) discussing whether to extend the sealing on a 'Triggerfish' warrant related to Ghislaine Maxwell. The seal is set to expire soon, and the New York office indicates they likely cannot justify seeking an extension. The warrant materials are attached.

events.title: Inquiry about Triggerfish Warrant Seal Extension
events.description: An email from the US Attorney's Office for the District of New Hampshire (USANH) inquires whether the seal on the Ghislaine Maxwell Triggerfish warrant needs to be extended, as it is set to expire soon.

events.title: Decision Not to Seek Extended Sealing
events.description: The US Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS) responds, stating they do not think they can justify seeking extended sealing on the Triggerfish warrant at that point.

keyFacts: The document references a 'Triggerfish' warrant related to Ghislaine Maxwell. A Triggerfish is a type of court order for real-time cell phone tracking.
The seal on this warrant was set to expire in late December 2020.
Prosecutors from the Southern District of New York (USANYS) concluded they could not justify seeking an extension of the seal at that time.
The email chain involves coordination between the US Attorney's Offices for the Southern District of New York (USANYS) and the District of New Hampshire (USANH).
The attached warrant materials are referenced but not included in the provided text.
